IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO ENRICH THE GREATER COMMUNITY THROUGH QUALITY SYMPHONIC PERFORMANCES AND EDUCATIONAL EXPERIENCES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE PURPOSE OF THE LUBBOCK SYMPHONY ORCHESTRA IS TO ENRICH THE GREATER COMMUNITY WE SERVE THROUGH QUALITY SYMPHONIC PERFORMANCES AND EDUCATIONAL EXPERIENCES.
IRS990.Desc: THE CONCERT SEASON INCLUDED BOTH A CLASSICAL AND CHAMBER SERIES WITH A HOLIDAY POPS AND SPECIAL CONCERTS FROM TIME TO TIME. THESE CONCERTS PROVIDE CULTURAL ACTIVITIES FOR THE ENTIRE SOUTH PLAINS REGION WITH OVER 14,000 IN ATTENDANCE EACH YEAR.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS INCLUDED A FREE FAMILY CONCERT, SIX ANNUAL EDUCATION CONCERTS WITH STUDENTS BUSSED INTO THE LUBBOCK MEMORIAL CIVIC CENTER, SMALL ENSEMBLES THAT PERFORM IN THE SCHOOLS, AND A TEACHING ARTIST PROGRAM THAT USES MUSIC TO TEACH CORE CURRICULA. THESE PROGRAMS REACH OVER 12,000 STUDENTS EACH YEAR IN THE SOUTH PLAINS REGION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL ENDOWMENT FUND EARNINGS ARE USED TO PROMOTE THE PROGRAMS AND MISSION OF THE LUBBOCK SYMPHONY ORCHESTRA.

THE ORGANIZATION HAS ADOPTED THE "UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS" PROVISIONS OF ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES GENERALLY ACCEPTED IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA. THE PRIMARY TAX POSITION OF THE ORGANIZATION IS ITS FILING STATUS AS A TAX EXEMPT ENTITY. THE ORGANIZATION DETERMINED THAT IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT THEIR TAX POSITIONS WOULD BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE (IRS), OR OTHER STATE TAXING AUTHORITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 4
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MINOR WORDING CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE FOLLOWING BY-LAW SECTIONS DURING 2017-2018. ARTICLE 3.5, 4.5.A.III, 4.5.B.II, 6, 7.1.A AND 7.2.G.2. FINALLY, A NEW SECTION 7.2.A.II WAS ADDED THAT READS, THE PLANNING COMMITTEE WORKS TO SELECT THE MUSIC DIRECTOR OF THE LUBBOCK SYMPHONY ORCHESTRA. THE COMMITTEE CONSISTS OF THE FOLLOWING INDIVIDUALS: PLANNING COMMITTEE CHAIR, CURRENT BOARD CHAIR, CURRENT BOARD CHAIR-ELECT, THREE MUSICIANS, DIRECTOR OF TTU SCHOOL OF MUSIC, TWO IMMEDIATE PAST CHAIRMEN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A COPY OF THE FORM 990 WILL BE PRESENTED TO THE TREASURER AND CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS FOR DISCUSSION, REVIEW AND APPROVAL PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ON AN ANNUAL BASIS, OFFICERS AND THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE REQUIRED TO REVIEW THE POLICIES OUTLINED IN THE ORGANIZATION'S CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND DISCLOSE ON THAT STATEMENT INFORMATION RELATING TO POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL REVIEW ALL SUCH STATEMENTS WITH A VIEW TO MINIMIZING THE POTENTIAL FOR ANY DETRIMENTAL EFFECTS FROM CONFLICTS AND EXCESS BENEFITS UNDER IRC SECTION 4958. ADDITIONALLY, OFFICERS AND BOARD DIRECTORS ARE REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE IN WRITING, ANY ACTION OR SITUATION THAT MIGHT VIOLATE THE POLICY TO THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS AS SOON AS POSSIBLE. WHEN A CONFLICT IS UNDER CONSIDERATION, NO INVOLVED DIRECTOR MAY BE PRESENT FOR THE DISCUSSION OF VOTE, NOR MAY ANY SUCH DIRECTOR INFLUENCE OR MAKE RECOMMENDATIONS WITH RESPECT TO SUCH VOTE. MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE NOT COMPENSATED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS USE A COMPENSATION SURVEY WHEN DETERMINING THE COMPENSATION OF THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR. THE PROCESS FOR DETERMINING THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTORS COMPENSATION IS DOCUMENTED IN THE BOARD MINUTES. CURRENTLY, EXCEPT FOR THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT HAVE ANY OTHER EMPLOYEES MEETING THE DEFINITION OF OFFICER OR KEY EMPLOYEE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE FOR VIEWING BY THE PUBLIC AT THE ORGANIZATION'S OFFICE IN LUBBOCK, TX.
